            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 6:12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", where it remained until the temple was built, when and which was the only time it was removed, whereas before it had been removed from place to place, and so till now had no rest; though some understand this of the ceasing or silence of the oracle over the ark, which was neither consulted by Solomon and his successors, nor any of the high priests afterwards (g). ",
            "children": []
